#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1573
msgid ""
"Units in Airbases do not count as aggressive if near a friendly city, and "
"can see further afield. Also, air units recover more hit points (a third per "
"turn, the same as in a city without an Airport)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1578
msgid ""
"Airbases have efficient anti-air weapons: units in an Airbase receive extra "
"defense (+100%) against air units and missiles. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1629
msgid ""
"Ruins mark the former site of a city that was destroyed or abandoned. They "
"have no effect on gameplay other than giving +1 trade bonus for the tile "
"with the ruins."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/terrain.ruleset:1658
msgid ""
"Roads allow your land units to move more quickly, and allow wheeled Big Land "
"units such as Chariots and Catapults to travel through otherwise difficult "
"terrain (Mountains, Jungle, and Swamp)."
